          "body": "Matthew 20:18-19 contains the fullest of the three passion predictions (cf. 16:21; 17:22-23). Jesus names six discrete elements: He will be (1) handed over to chief priests and scribes, (2) condemned to death, (3) handed over to Gentiles, (4) mocked, (5) scourged, (6) crucified — and on the third day raised. Every element will be fulfilled within the week. This is not vague foreboding; it is prophetic precision. The disciples' response, however, is to immediately request thrones (20:20-21). Matthew's juxtaposition is devastating. They heard the words and did not register them. The Twelve are functionally as blind as the beggars at Jericho — only the beggars know they are blind."
